gomodel:SYNGO_544  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 3c,d\nLRRTM4 localizes to the postsynaptic density of glutamatergic synapses\nLiteral\n\"LRRTM4 puncta partially overlapped with the presynaptic excitatory marker VGlut1 (Figure 3C) and colocalized with the postsynaptic glutamate receptor subunit GluR1 (Figure 3D).\"\n\n15/5/2017 Pim\n- There is reason to interpret the low-resolution data to support post-synaptic localization of LRRTM4.\n\n1. Literal: \"The LRRTM4 transcript is only expressed in DG granule cells in this region (Figure 3A), suggesting that LRRTM4 localizes to granule cell dendrites\" --> in the postsynaptic neuron\n2. Literal: \" LRRTM4 puncta partially overlapped with the presynaptic excitatory marker VGlut1 (Figure 3C) and colocalized with the postsynaptic glutamate receptor subunit GluR1 (Figure 3D).\" -> sign of localization in synaptic cleft.\n\nAuthors conclude: \"These data suggest that endogenous LRRTM4 localizes to the postsynaptic density of glutamatergic synapses\". Experimental description: Literal from M&M\n\"Hippocampal neurons were cultured from P0 Long-Evans rats (Charles River)\nand plated on poly-D-lysine-coated (Millipore) and laminin-coated (Invitrogen)\nchamber slides\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_544" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

